text.section:
The department may, following a hearing pursuant to KRS Chapter 13B, impose sanctions specified in KRS 227A.040 upon proof that the licensee has:
Misrepresented or concealed a material fact in obtaining a license, or in the reinstatement thereof;
Been incompetent or negligent in the practice of performing electrical work;
Failed to comply with an order issued by the department or an assurance of voluntary compliance; or
Violated any provisions of KRS 227A.010 to 227A.140 and administrative regulations promulgated thereunder.
